; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> press release</a>. =
Did he? Is that what happened? If you are an investment manager for Florida=
 and you are convinced that climate change is a material risk factor for so=
me companies, can=E2=80=99t you still consider that risk? As a pecuniary fa=
ctor, not an ideological one?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A certain amount of the ESG fight will take th=
e form of broad public statements of principles. BlackRock will say =E2=80=
=9Cwe need a fundamental reshaping of finance that puts sustainability at t=
he center,=E2=80=9D and Republicans will say =E2=80=9Cwe need to crack down=
 on woke capital,=E2=80=9D and BlackRock will say =E2=80=9Cdid we say funda=
mental reshaping of finance, whoops, no, we just meant fiduciary considerat=
ion of material risk factors.=E2=80=9D But a lot of it will take the form (=
and has <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/28834876.2=
58574/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8wNS8yOC9idXNpbmVzcy9kZWFsYm9va=
