rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> already taken the form</a>) of fact-intensive debates about particular =
investment decisions. Some investment manager will say =E2=80=9Cwe are unde=
rweight oil and gas companies because we are concerned about the financial =
impact of climate transition risk,=E2=80=9D and some state regulator will s=
ay =E2=80=9Cwe think=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s actually=C2=A0because you are enviro=
nmentalists,=E2=80=9D and the investment manager will say =E2=80=9Cno here =
is our investment model that considers environmental risk as a factor in as=
sessing risk and returns,=E2=80=9D and the regulator will say =E2=80=9Cwe t=
hink that you are using inappropriately long investment horizons and imprud=
ently weighting this risk in your calculation,=E2=80=9D and the manager wil=
l provide support for its view, and they=E2=80=99ll go back and forth. Ever=
y financial decision can also become a political argument. It seems exhaust=
ing.</p>
